Given a string of lowercase letters in the range ascii[a-z], determine the index of a character that can be
removed to make the string a palindrome. There may be more than one solution, but any will do. If the w
is already a palindrome or there is no solution, return -1. Otherwise, return the index of a character to re
Example
s "bcbc"
Either remove 'b' at index 0 or 'c' at index 3.
Function Description
Complete the palindrome/ndexfunction in the editor below.
palindromelndex has the following parameter(s):
• strings: a string to analyze
Returns
• int:the index of the character to remove or —1
Input Format
The first line contains an integer q, the number of queries.
Each of the next q lines contains a query string s.